In this article, President Obama challenges governors to invest more in education to ensure American students and workers are prepared for the jobs of the 21st century. The White House also released an Education Blueprint, which highlights the administration's efforts in education and shows that many states have cut spending on higher education and elementary/secondary schools. The report emphasizes the importance of a strong education system for the American economy, especially during times of economic challenge. The President calls for a shared commitment to education, urging governors to pressure Congress to pass his proposals to prevent teacher layoffs, make college more affordable, and invest in the nation's education system. The President believes that critical investments in education are necessary to create an economy that is built to last and provides equal opportunities for all.